<DocsLayout title="Wire into Claude Code" slug="usage/mcp-claude" description="Configure Claude Code, Cursor, or any MCP client to talk to Skill Wiki.">
  <h1>Wire into Claude Code</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--fg-muted);">
    The MCP server runs locally and talks to your agent over stdio. Same shape works
    for Cursor, Continue, Aider, or any MCP-capable client — only the config file
    location differs.
  </p>

  <h2>Claude Code</h2>
  <p>Edit <code>~/.config/claude-code/mcp.json</code> (macOS / Linux) or the equivalent on Windows:</p>

<pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "skill-wiki": {
      "command": "bunx",
      "args": ["@prime-lang/mcp-server-core"],
      "env": {
        "PRIME_DIR": "/abs/path/to/your/primes/compiled"
      }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>

  <p>Restart Claude Code. The 5 tools should appear in the agent's tool list:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>prime_query</code></li>
    <li><code>prime_resolve</code></li>
    <li><code>prime_intent</code></li>
    <li><code>prime_validate</code></li>
    <li><code>prime_compile</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cursor</h2>
<pre><code>{`# Cursor settings → MCP servers → Add
Server name: skill-wiki
Command:     bunx
Args:        @prime-lang/mcp-server-core
Env:         PRIME_DIR=/abs/path/to/compiled`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Continue</h2>
  <p>Edit <code>~/.continue/config.json</code>:</p>

<pre><code>{`{
  "experimental": {
    "modelContextProtocolServers": [
      {
        "transport": {
          "type": "stdio",
          "command": "bunx",
          "args": ["@prime-lang/mcp-server-core"]
        },
        "env": {
          "PRIME_DIR": "/abs/path/to/compiled"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}`}</code></pre>

  <h2>HTTP transport</h2>
  <p>For browser-based clients or shared deployments:</p>

<pre><code>{`# Server side
PRIME_DIR=/abs/path/to/compiled \\
  bunx @prime-lang/mcp-server-core --http --port 4001

# Client side — connect to http://your-host:4001/mcp`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Test the connection</h2>
  <p>Once connected, ask the agent something the corpus knows:</p>

<blockquote>
  <em>"What atoms in the corpus describe a 'pan sauce'? Use prime_query."</em>
</blockquote>

  <p>The agent should return a list of atoms, each with a kind and projection path,
  and may follow up by calling <code>Read</code> to load specific bodies.</p>

  <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Likely cause</th><th>Fix</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>No tools appear</td><td>Config file not loaded</td><td>Check the file path; restart the client</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>spawn bunx ENOENT</code></td><td>Bun not installed or not in PATH</td><td>Install bun globally or use absolute path</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>PRIME_DIR not found</code></td><td>Path doesn't point to compiled output</td><td>Run <code>prime compile</code> first</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Hits return but body fails to load</td><td>Agent's <code>Read</code> tool can't reach the path</td><td>Use absolute paths in <code>PRIME_DIR</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
